dfdl:alignmentUnits.description: alignment value can be units of bits or units of bytes

dfdl:lengthUnits.description: lengthUnits value can be specified as bits, bytes, or characters

dfdl:representation.description: representation value can be binary or text

dfdl:binaryNumberRep.description: binaryNumberRep value can be binary, packed, bcd, or ibm4690Packed

dfdl:bitOrder.description: bitOrder value can be mostSignificantBitFirst or leastSignificantBitFirst

dfdl:lengthKind.description: lengthKind value can be explicit, delimited, implicit, prefixed, pattern, endOfParent

dfdl:alignment.description: alignment value can have a value of 1 or implicit

dfdl:encodingErrorPolicy.description: encodingErrorPolicy value can be error or replace

dfdl:calendarPatternKind.description: calendarPatterKnid value can be explicit or implicit

dfdl:documentTerminatorCanBeMissing.description: documentFinalTerminatorCanBeMissing value can be yes or no

dfdl:emptyValueDelimiterPolicy.description: emptyValueDelimiterPolicy value can be initiator, terminator, both, none

dfdl:escapeSchemeRef.description: a named escape scheme definition via its qualified name

dfdl:fillByte.description: A single byte specified as a DFDL byte value entity or a single character.

dfdl:.description: float value can be yes or no

dfdl:ignoreCase.description: ignoreCase value can be no or yes

dfdl:initiatedContent.description: initiatedContent value can be no or yes

dfdl:leadingSkip.description: A non-negative number of bytes or bits to skip before alignment is applied

dfdl:separator.description: Specifies a whitespace separated list of alternative DFDL String Literals that are the possible separators for the sequence

dfdl:separatorPolicy.description: SeparatorPolicy value can be required, suppressed or suppressedAtEnd

dfdl:separatorSuppressionPolicy.description: separatorSupressionPolicy value can be anyEmpty, never, trailingEmpty or trailingEmptyStrict

dfdl:outputNewLine.description: outputNewLine value can be %CR, %LF or both(%CR,%LF)

dfdl:textStandardZeroRep.description: testStandardZeroRep values can be an empty string or any character string

dfdl:textStandardInfinityRep.description: The value used to represent infinity

dfdl:textStandardNaNRep.description: The value used to represent NaN

dfdl:textStandardExponentRep.description: Defines the actual character(s) that appear in the data as the exponent indicator

dfdl:textStandardGroupingSeparator.description: This property defines the single character that can appear in the data as the grouping separator

dfdl:textNumberPattern.description: Defines the ICU-like pattern that describes the format of the text number

dfdl:textNumberRounding.description: textNumberRounding value can be explicit or pattern

dfdl:textNumberRoundingMode.description: textNumberRoundingMode value can be rondCeiling, roundFloor, roundDown, roundUp, roundHalfEven, roundHalfDown, roundHalfUp, or roundUnneccessary

dfdl:textNumberRoundingIncrement.description: Specifies the rounding increment to use during unparsing

dfdl:separatorPosition.description: separatorPosition can be infix, postfix or prefix

dfdl:sequenceKind.description: sequenceKind values can be ordered or unordered

dfdl:terminator.description: expresses characters or bytes to be found in the data stream to mark the termination of an element

dfdl:textBidi.description: Future property that will allow bi-direction text processing. Current valid value is no

dfdl:textNumberCheckPolicy.description: textNumberCheckPolicy value can be lax or strict

dfdl:textNumberRep.description: textNumberRep value can be standard or zoned

dfdl:textOutputMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum content length during unparsing for simple types that do not allow the XSD minLength facet to be specified

dfdl:textPadKind.description: textPadKind value can be none or padChar

dfdl:textStandardBase.description: Indicates the number base valid values are 2, 8, 10, or 16

dfdl:textTrimKind.description: textTrimKind value can be none or padChar

dfdl:trailingSkip.description: A non-negative number of bytes or bits to skip after the element

dfdl:truncateSpecifiedLengthString.description: truncateSpecifiedLengthString value can be yes or no

dfdl:utf16Width.description: utf16width value can be fixrd or variable

dfdl:encoding.description: encoding value can be Us-ASCII, ASCII, UTF-8, UTF-16, UTF-16BE, UTF-16LE, ISO-8859-1

dfdl:nilKind.description: nilKind value can be literalCharacter, literalValue or logicalValue

dfdl:nilValueDelimiterPolicy.description: nilValueDelimiterPolicy value can be initiator, terminator, both, or none

dfdl:occursCountKind.description: occursCountKind value can be expression, fixed, implicit, parsed, stopValue

dfdl:choiceLengthKind.description: choiceLengthKind value can be explicit or implicit

xs:complexType2.description: dfdl complexType block with name attribute

xs:sequencehiddengroup.description: dfdl sequence block with hidden group

dfdl:discriminator.description: dfdl:discriminator is used during parsing to: 1.resolve points of uncertainty 2.remove ambiguity during speculative parsing 3.improve diagnostic behavior when a DFDL parser encounters malformed data. A DFDL discriminator may contain a test expression that evaluates to true or false.

dfdl:inputValueCalc.description: An expression that calculates the value of the element when parsing.

dfdl:outputValueCalc.description: An expression that calculates the value of the current element when parsing.
